<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,756,1926,2077]" lastBlockId="1.[831,1437,257,699]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" box="[273,434,1928,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,434,1928,1950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[451,498,1926,1950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Zeller, 1866" authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuhlweinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora kuhlweinii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zeller P. C." box="[268,399,1957,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="137 - 157" refId="ref8528" refString="Zeller P. C. 1866. Beschreibung einiger amerikanischen Wickler und Crambiden. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 27 (4 - 6): 137 - 157." type="journal article" year="1866">Zeller, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) is presently known to include 15 species from the Old and New Worlds (
<bibRefCitation author="Nuss M. &amp; Landry B. &amp; Mally R. &amp; Vegliante F. &amp; Trankner A. &amp; Bauer F. &amp; Hayden J. &amp; Segerer A. &amp; Schouten R. &amp; Li H. &amp; Trofimova T. &amp; Solis M. A. &amp; De Prins J. &amp; Speidel W. &amp; Global Information System on Pyraloidea" box="[563,744,1989,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" refId="ref8356" refString="Nuss M., Landry B., Mally R., Vegliante F., Trankner A., Bauer F., Hayden J., Segerer A., Schouten R., Li H., Trofimova T., Solis M. A., De Prins J., Speidel W. 2003 - 2020. Global Information System on Pyraloidea. www. pyraloidea. org. Last accessed 01 / 05 / 2020." type="book" year="2020">
Nuss 
<emphasis box="[623,675,1992,2014]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
, 2020
</bibRefCitation>
), although the Old World species placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" box="[594,755,2023,2045]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[594,755,2023,2045]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably belong in fact to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1938" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1938" box="[438,753,2053,2077]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glaucocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[438,583,2055,2077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Glaucocharis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick E." box="[591,753,2053,2077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="426 - 429" refId="ref8328" refString="Meyrick E. 1938. New Species of New Zealand Lepidoptera. Transactions and Proceedings of the Royal Society of New Zealand 67: 426 - 429." type="journal article" year="1938">Meyrick, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The New World fauna of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" box="[1120,1281,260,282]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1120,1281,260,282]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes nine described species (
<bibRefCitation author="Nuss M. &amp; Landry B. &amp; Mally R. &amp; Vegliante F. &amp; Trankner A. &amp; Bauer F. &amp; Hayden J. &amp; Segerer A. &amp; Schouten R. &amp; Li H. &amp; Trofimova T. &amp; Solis M. A. &amp; De Prins J. &amp; Speidel W. &amp; Global Information System on Pyraloidea" box="[1042,1242,290,314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" refId="ref8356" refString="Nuss M., Landry B., Mally R., Vegliante F., Trankner A., Bauer F., Hayden J., Segerer A., Schouten R., Li H., Trofimova T., Solis M. A., De Prins J., Speidel W. 2003 - 2020. Global Information System on Pyraloidea. www. pyraloidea. org. Last accessed 01 / 05 / 2020." type="book" year="2020">
Nuss 
<emphasis box="[1109,1162,292,314]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
., 2020
</bibRefCitation>
) that occur from the southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1320,322,346]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">
United States of 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[1228,1320,322,346]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="America" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Arizona">America</taxonomicName>
</collectingCountry>
(Arizona) south to the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1045,1200,354,378]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
in the south of 
<collectingCountry box="[1364,1433,354,378]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The Neotropical fauna was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gaskin D. E." box="[1261,1433,386,410]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="107 - 123" refId="ref7938" refString="Gaskin D. E. 1986 a. Genus Diptychophora Zeller and a related new genus Steneromene from the Neotropical Region (Pyralidae: Crambinae). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 40 (2): 107 - 123." type="journal article" year="1986">Gaskin (1986a)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Landry B." box="[831,989,418,442]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="1071 - 1077" refId="ref8139" refString="Landry B. 1990. Two new species of Diptychophora from Mexico (Lepidoptera: Pyralidae: Crambinae: Diptychophorini). The Canadian Entomologist 122 (11 - 12): 1071 - 1077." type="journal article" year="1990">Landry (1990)</bibRefCitation>
added two new species and 
<bibRefCitation author="Solis M. A." box="[1303,1436,418,442]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="493 - 504" refId="ref8438" refString="Solis M. A. 2009. Transfer of all Western Hemisphere Cybalomiinae to other subfamilies (Crambidae: Pyraloidea: Lepidoptera): Elusia Schaus, Dichochroma Forbes, Schacontia Dyar, Cybalomia extorris Warren, and C. lojanalis (Dognin). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 111 (2): 493 - 504." type="journal article" year="2009">Solis (2009)</bibRefCitation>
transferred an additional species from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marion" authorityYear="1955" box="[1256,1406,450,474]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cybalomiinae">Cybalomiinae</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" box="[831,992,484,506]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[831,992,484,506]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although synapomorphies have not been presented for the genus yet, 
<taxonomicName authority="Landry (1990)" authorityName="Landry" authorityYear="1990" box="[1152,1437,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="powelli">
<emphasis box="[1152,1267,517,539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">D. powelli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Landry B." box="[1278,1437,514,539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="1071 - 1077" refId="ref8139" refString="Landry B. 1990. Two new species of Diptychophora from Mexico (Lepidoptera: Pyralidae: Crambinae: Diptychophorini). The Canadian Entomologist 122 (11 - 12): 1071 - 1077." type="journal article" year="1990">Landry (1990)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as well as the species transferred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Solis M. A." box="[1251,1389,547,571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="493 - 504" refId="ref8438" refString="Solis M. A. 2009. Transfer of all Western Hemisphere Cybalomiinae to other subfamilies (Crambidae: Pyraloidea: Lepidoptera): Elusia Schaus, Dichochroma Forbes, Schacontia Dyar, Cybalomia extorris Warren, and C. lojanalis (Dognin). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 111 (2): 493 - 504." type="journal article" year="2009">Solis (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dognin, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Dognin" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[831,1141,579,603]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lojanalis">
<emphasis box="[831,961,581,603]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">D. lojanalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dognin P." box="[978,1134,579,603]" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" pagination="61 - 90" refId="ref7911" refString="Dognin P. 1905. Heteroceres nouveaux de l'Amerique du Sud. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, Bruxelles 49: 61 - 90." type="journal article" year="1905">Dognin, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, do not exhibit the typical valva shape of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" box="[1007,1168,613,635]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1168,613,635]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and hence may require new genera or transfers to other existing genera. No larval host is presently known for the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeller" authorityYear="1866" box="[1268,1429,677,699]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Diptychophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1268,1429,677,699]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="74">Diptychophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
